This paper deals with a scheduling problem over a time-varying channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The problem is formulated as a dynamic program, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the optimality of different policies, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG) concepts.
